<script id="gtm-jq-ajax-listen" type="text/javascript">
  (function() {

    'use strict';
	var $;
    var n = 0;
    init();

    function init(n) {

      // Ensure jQuery is available before anything
      if (typeof jQuery !== 'undefined') {
		
        // Define our $ shortcut locally
        $ = jQuery;
        bindToAjax();

      // Check for up to 10 seconds
      } else if (n < 20) {
	
        n++;
        setTimeout(init, 500);

      }

    }

    function bindToAjax() {

      $(document).bind('ajaxComplete', function(evt, jqXhr, opts) {

        // Create a fake a element for magically simple URL parsing
        var fullUrl = document.createElement('a');
        fullUrl.href = opts.url;

        // IE9+ strips the leading slash from a.pathname because who wants to get home on time Friday anyways
        var pathname = fullUrl.pathname[0] === '/' ? fullUrl.pathname : '/' + fullUrl.pathname;
        // Manually remove the leading question mark, if there is one
        var queryString = fullUrl.search[0] === '?' ? fullUrl.search.slice(1) : fullUrl.search;
        // Turn our params and headers into objects for easier reference
        var queryParameters = objMap(queryString, '&', '=', true);
        var headers = objMap(jqXhr.getAllResponseHeaders(), '\n', ':');

        // Blindly push to the dataLayer because this fires within GTM
        dataLayer.push({
          'event': 'ajaxComplete',
          'attributes': {
            // Return empty strings to prevent accidental inheritance of old data
            'type': opts.type || '',
            'url': fullUrl.href || '',
            'queryParameters': queryParameters,
            'pathname': pathname || '',
            'hostname': fullUrl.hostname || '',
            'protocol': fullUrl.protocol || '',
            'fragment': fullUrl.hash || '',
            'statusCode': jqXhr.status || '',
            'statusText': jqXhr.statusText || '',
            'headers': headers,
            'timestamp': evt.timeStamp || '',
            'contentType': opts.contentType || '',
            // Defer to jQuery's handling of the response
            'response': (jqXhr.responseJSON || jqXhr.responseXML || jqXhr.responseText || '')
          }
        });

      });

    }

    function objMap(data, delim, spl, decode) {

      var obj = {};

      // If one of our parameters is missing, return an empty object
      if (!data || !delim || !spl) {

        return {};

      }

      var arr = data.split(delim);
      var i;

      if (arr) {

        for (i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {

          // If the decode flag is present, URL decode the set
          var item = decode ? decodeURIComponent(arr[i]) : arr[i];
          var pair = item.split(spl);

          var key = trim_(pair[0]);
          var value = trim_(pair[1]);

          if (key && value) {

            obj[key] = value;

          }

        }

      }

      return obj;

    }

    // Basic .trim() polyfill
    function trim_(str) {

      if (str) {

        return str.replace(/^[\s\uFEFF\xA0]+|[\s\uFEFF\xA0]+$/g, '');

      }

    }


  })();
  /*

   * Documentation: http://www.lunametrics.com/blog/2015/08/27/ajax-event-listener-google-tag-manager/
   * Licensed under the Creative Commons 4.0 Attribution Public License
   */
</script>

<script type="text/javascript" id="gtm-cookie-remover">
  /*
   * Cookie Remover
   * Script for remving cookies within GTM using Custom HTML Tags
   *
   * Instructions:
   * To remove a cookie, create a Custom HTML Tag that pushes data about
   * the cookie into the dataLayer.
   *
   * <script>
   * dataLayer.push({
   *   'event': 'removeCookie',
   *   'attributes': {
   *     'cookieName': 'myCookie',       // Required.
   *     'cookiePath': '/',              // Opt. Defaults to '/'. Must match stored cookie.
   *     'cookieDomain': 'example.com',  // Opt. Defaults to hostname of page. Must match stored cookie.
   *   }
   * });
   * <\/script>
   *
   * If the cookie doesn't appear to be removed, check the path and hostname of the
   * stored cookie, as these values must match in order to successfully remove it.
   */
  (function(document) {

	var attributes = {{DLV - attributes - v1}};
    var cookieName    = attributes.cookieName;  // Name of the cookie; preferred syntax is all lowercase, with no spaces
    var cookieDomain  = attributes.cookieDomain;  // Hostname cookie is stored on
    var cookiePath    = attributes.cookiePath; // Path cookie is stored at.
        
    if(typeof cookieName !== 'undefined') {
       
        document.cookie = cookieName + '=; Expires=Thu, 01 Jan 1970 00:00:01 GMT'
                        + (cookieDomain ? '; Domain=' + cookieDomain : '') 
                        + (cookiePath ? '; Path=' + cookiePath : '');
        
    }
    
  })(document);
  /*
   * v1.0.0
   * Created by the Google Analytics consultants at http://www.lunametrics.com
   * Written by @notdanwilkerson
   * Licensed under the MIT License
   */
</script>

<script type="text/javascript" id="gtm-cookie-setter">
  /*
   * Cookie Setter
   * Script for setting cookies within GTM using Custom HTML Tags
   *
   * Instructions:
   * To set a cookie, create a Custom HTML Tag that pushes data about
   * the cookie into the dataLayer.
   *
   * <script>
   * dataLayer.push({
   *   'event': 'setCookie',
   *   'attributes': {
   *     'cookieName': 'myCookie',        // Required.
   *     'cookieValue': '12345',          // Required.
   *     'cookiePath': '/',               // Opt. Defaults to '/'.
   *     'cookieDomain': 'example.com',  // Opt. Defaults to hostname of page
   *     'cookieExpires': 30              // Opt. Set in days. Default is after browser closes.
   *   }
   * });
   * <\/script>
   *
   * For 99% of uses cases, cookiePath should be '/', and cookieDomain should be
   * 'domainname.tld', e.g. for 'shop.example.com' you would use 'example.com'.
   * If you need the cookie to expire in less than a day, provide a fraction
   * or division for cookieExpires, e.g. a 30 minute expiration would be: 1 / 48
   */
  (function(document) {

    var attributes = {{DLV - attributes - v1}};
    var cookieName    = attributes.cookieName;  // Name of the cookie; preferred syntax is all lowercase, with no spaces
    var cookieValue   = encodeURIComponent(attributes.cookieValue);  // The value stored with the cookie. Is automatically encoded. Check 'Decode cookie value' when using with 1st Party Cookie Variable
    var cookieExpires = parseFloat(attributes.cookieExpires);  // Expiration length in terms of days. Defaults to expiring when the browser closes. Can accept a fraction for > 1 day time periods, e.g. 1/48 (30 minutes)
    var cookieDomain  = attributes.cookieDomain;  // Hostname to store the cookie on. Defaults to browser handling.
    var cookiePath    = attributes.cookiePath || '/'; // Path to store cookie at. Defaults to '/'.
        
    var expirationDate = '';

    if(!isNaN(cookieExpires) && cookieExpires !== 0) {

      expirationDate = "; Expires=" + new Date(+new Date() + 1000 * 60 * 60 * 24 * cookieExpires).toGMTString();

    }

    if(typeof cookieName !== 'undefined' && typeof cookieValue !== 'undefined') {

      document.cookie = cookieName + '=' +
                        cookieValue +
                        expirationDate +
                        (cookieDomain ? '; Domain=' + cookieDomain : '') +
                        (cookiePath ? '; Path=' + cookiePath  : '');

    }
    
  })(document);
  /*
   * v1.0.0
   * Created by the Google Analytics consultants at http://www.lunametrics.com
   * Written by @notdanwilkerson
   * Licensed under the MIT License
   */
</script>
